Class ClassChecker.MethodInfoCollector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor
      • org.apache.felix.ipojo.manipulation.ClassChecker.MethodInfoCollector
  • Enclosing class:
    ClassChecker

    private final class ClassChecker.MethodInfoCollector
extends org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor
    This class collects annotations in a method. This class creates an ClassChecker.AnnotationDescriptor if an annotation is found during the visit. It also collects local variables definition.
    Author:
    Felix Project Team

    • Method Detail

      • visitAnnotation

        public org.objectweb.asm.AnnotationVisitor visitAnnotation(String name,
                                                           boolean visible)
        Visits an annotation. This class checks the visibility. If the annotation is visible, creates the ClassChecker.AnnotationDescriptor corresponding to this annotation to visit this annotation. This ClassChecker.AnnotationDescriptor is added to the MethodDescriptor of the visited method.
        Overrides:
        visitAnnotation in class org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the annotation
        visible - is the annotation visible at runtime
        Returns:
        the ClassChecker.AnnotationDescriptor to visit this annotation or null if the annotation is not visible.
        See Also:
        MethodVisitor.visitAnnotation(java.lang.String, boolean)
